00:38:41.211 --> 00:38:44.756
And I was trying to really be present and focused and not distracted.

00:38:44.776 --> 00:38:47.099
So I turned my phone off and left it on the beach chair.

00:38:47.159 --> 00:38:52.787
And we went to the edge of the water and I was trying to care about what Clover cared about and what Clover cared about was seashells.

00:38:53.328 --> 00:38:55.251
And she said, daddy, I want to get some seashells.

00:38:55.271 --> 00:38:57.554
And of course I go, where are we going to keep them?

00:38:57.698 --> 00:39:00.982
pulls out a Ziploc baggie and that she had produced out of her bathing suit.

00:39:01.943 --> 00:39:02.964
Cause that's Clover, right?

00:39:03.044 --> 00:39:03.765
Always a plan.

00:39:04.125 --> 00:39:09.731
She goes, they're going to go in this bag that I brought for the seashells that I planned to, you know, pick up.

00:39:10.552 --> 00:39:18.822
And so we walked around and I got to admit Clover was better at picking up seashells than dad cause I was having a hard time finding any, but she had so many in the bag already.

00:39:18.842 --> 00:39:19.823
And she goes, what's the matter with you?

00:39:19.843 --> 00:39:20.563
You haven't contributed any.

00:39:20.583 --> 00:39:21.484
I said, I can't find any.

00:39:21.765 --> 00:39:22.385
I can't find any.

00:39:22.406 --> 00:39:23.106
All these are broken.

00:39:23.146 --> 00:39:26.450
And she goes, dad, the broken seashells are beautiful too.

00:39:31.010 --> 00:39:36.878
That was worth the price of admission right there, church.

00:39:36.918 --> 00:39:40.584
Come on, thank God that he sees beauty in your broken places.

00:39:43.187 --> 00:39:47.954
He still puts us in his bag and has a plan to bring us home, even though we're broken.

